<br>
The faster a person or object moves the slower time goes. If you spend your whole life driving around your cells will be slightly younger than that of a person born on the same day as yourself who sat on their @ss all their life. <br>
<br>
Anyone can move forward in time, but its generally at a constant rate.<br>
<br>
There has been suggestions that with the creation of a worm hole we have two points in time which a person can move between but they can not travel through time prior to when the worm hole was created.<br>
<br>
If absolute zero was achieved then matter will collapse in on itself and a blackhole would be created, if the whole universe reached absolute zero then I guess time would stop, but so would the existance of life.<br>
<br>
Thats kind of fragmented but Im too tired to change any of that. I'll leave you all with a last question. If.. say... time travel was possible and I could travel back in time to when my grandfather was a kid (before he had kids) and I shot him dead, what would happen. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=coldkodiak>ColdKodiak</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://godkodiak.homestead.com/files/face.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/8/03 2:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12731.topic&index=42>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://godkodiak.homestead.com/files/avatar.jpg height=130 width=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ouch!</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> If.. say... time travel was possible and I could travel back in time to when my grandfather was a kid (before he had kids) and I shot him dead, what would happen. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
