<br>
I watched some show on some channel and it was steven hawking and a buncha other guys all talking about time travel.<br>
<br>
Apparently if you travel through time, you appear as yourself, if this is true then it explains spontaneous human combustion, because to travel through time you have to travel extremely fast, and your molecules colliding with your own molecules causes this combustion, of course that is only if you are travelling forward. Or that when you time travel, you enter another dimension(for the sake of simplicity) to the left of this one, so nothing may be different except for the placement of a strand of hair, or nuclear war has ensued killing all life.<br>
<br>
Aside from that, I guess according to theory there are atoms at the edge of the universe that pass through the whole timestream and back in constant loop faster than the atoms that make us up, kinda like a record spins faster on the edge than the center. SO if you took billions of these atoms and turned them into silverizer for a mirror. And created a mirror with them, then you set it in an arbitrary place and looked at it. Would you see everything that would happen ever?<br>
<br>
Now onto mirrors. If you make a one-way mirror sphere, what would you see in it(bieng that the mirror side is inside)?<br>
Now if you took a one-way mirror sphere and placed it inside a larger one-way mirror sphere then created a suit to somehow blend yourself seamlessly to mirror completely over your whole body and you got inside the large sphere, what would you see inside the  smaller sphere?<br>
<br>
Most of this stuff was thought up really late at night, so if it sounds bizzarre or inaccurate, maybe it is. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.geocities.com/gaara_sunakage/NARUTOdraw.txt" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=agentcryrid>Agent Cryrid</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/10/03 11:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12731.topic&index=44>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://sc.groups.msn.com/tn/E6/91/SaiyajinsBloodRPG/1/1.jpg height=96 width=83></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ouch!</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Apparently if you travel through time, you appear as yourself, if this is true then it explains spontaneous human combustion<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
