<br>
Does that mean there are millions of every person?<br>
<br>
Also, another question: about perception. When you start to cross a road, in 'this' dimension, you are you and you perceive the world from your point of view. now, when you stop crossing that road (i.e. reach other side), what determined that you, as you are perceiving the world now, be the one of you that is in the dimension whereby you survived? Also, when someone does die, what determines that they be the one that didn't survive? obviously that can't really be answered...I guess all I'm saying is that the number of times you crossed the road and made it to the other side, you must be really, really, really lucky to be the half of you that survived every time. Chance alone would have it the other way. <br>
<br>
One last question: If the dimension really does branch like that at every possible 'other' option, well, where does the matter come to form that whole other dimension? or is that one of those incomprehensible things where the matter in each dimension is the same but rearranged matter and that the any given atom is in more than one dimension at once? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=theandroid@polykarbonbbs>the android</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/12/03 1:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12731.topic&index=52>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:</span><hr size=1> according to that particular theory, every choice in the universe sprouts a new universe based on a possible outcome of a situation, so yea there are millions of universes being created and millions of 'you's' in those universes, If i'm not mistaken, the theory is sometimes called the many-verse theory. <br>
<br>
Ever watched sliders? thats based on the manyverse concept, however it doesn't concern itself about time. In fact its completely irrelevant to the subject of time travel. I posted that because some (i'm not too good with your names yet, my sincere apologies) said something about the shape of time. But that is just one theory.<br>
