About your last question, I can't really answer that because I've not researched that particular point enough, what I can explain is another theory, that the universe is actually just the expansion of a hydrogen atom. Which means our universe may be part of a rock on some planet which exist in an even bigger universe! Have you seen men in Black, the universes are these marbles, well thats another theory which I don't quite understand, but I would think that the matter is formed through external (to our universe) processes which cause our universe to gain energy, thus in its expansion, new atoms are created, but then this would mean that there is a tremendous deal of external processes!!!....I honestly don't know, the answers cause paradox which is why these are all just theories. <br>
